  <li id="comment-37802" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Sara</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/06/told-you-so/#comment-37802"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-07-11T19:57:24-04:00">Thursday, July 11, 2013 at 7:57 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve visited three friends in the last week who had this cookbook so I&#39;ve spent some time perusing it and knew I wanted to make this recipe right away.  I was though, I have to admit, a little taken aback by the sheer number of calories in one serving (after plugging it into my tracker).  To try and lighten it up a bit, I cut back the amount of oil (I used about 4 tbsp total &#8211; 2 in the sauce and 2 in the pan), which didn&#39;t give me oil to drizzle over, but that&#39;s fine.  I also did a mixture of yogurts &#8211; 1 cup of non-fat and 2 cups of 2%, and I decreased the amount of feta just a bit (mostly because the package I bought was only 6oz, which was really plenty).  I used a bigger pasta &#8211; a whole wheat orecchiette&#8211; and I probably could have gotten 7 or 8 servings out of the whole thing.  Finally, I didn&#39;t have pine nuts, but used pistachios and they were fantastic.  Even with those changes, this was incredibly rich and flavorful, so I don&#39;t feel like I was missing out.  It&#39;s serving double duty as leftovers for lunch.  So tasty and really quick and easy!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-37890" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Sara</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/06/told-you-so/#comment-37890"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-07-11T19:57:24-04:00">Thursday, July 11, 2013 at 7:57 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve visited three friends in the last week who had this cookbook so I&#39;ve spent some time perusing it and knew I wanted to make this recipe right away.  I was though, I have to admit, a little taken aback by the sheer number of calories in one serving (after plugging it into my tracker).  To try and lighten it up a bit, I cut back the amount of oil (I used about 4 tbsp total &#8211; 2 in the sauce and 2 in the pan), which didn&#39;t give me oil to drizzle over, but that&#39;s fine.  I also did a mixture of yogurts &#8211; 1 cup of non-fat and 2 cups of 2%, and I decreased the amount of feta just a bit (mostly because the package I bought was only 6oz, which was really plenty).  I used a bigger pasta &#8211; a whole wheat orecchiette&#8211; and I probably could have gotten 7 or 8 servings out of the whole thing.  Finally, I didn&#39;t have pine nuts, but used pistachios and they were fantastic.  Even with those changes, this was incredibly rich and flavorful, so I don&#39;t feel like I was missing out.  It&#39;s serving double duty as leftovers for lunch.  So tasty and really quick and easy!</p>
    </div>

